<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="precise-adj">precise <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /prɪ'saɪs/    美 /prɪ'saɪs/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-exact">1.★ <strong>精确的；准确的；确切的 (exact)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a precise record of events 
对事件的准确记载</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It was found at the precise spot where she had left it.
那件东西正好在她遗落的那个地点找到了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>(人) 细心的；精细的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a precise worker 
一丝不苟的工作者</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>precisely  /prɪ'saɪsli/ adv   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is difficult to <strong>know precisely</strong> how much impact the changes will have. 
很难准确了解这些变化会造成多大影响。</p></div></div>